Boil a full kettle.

Pour most of the @boiled water{150%ml} into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat, reserving some for the sauce later.

Add the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12-13%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, trim the @pak choi{1%unit}, then thinly slice widthways.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British Beef Mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat.

Add the pak choi to the mince.

Stir-fry until just soft, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir the @Yellow Thai Style Paste{45%g}, @Soy Sauce{15%ml}, @Peanut Butter{30%g}, @Ketjap Manis{50%g}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and reserved boiled water for the sauce to the frying pan.

Bring to the boil, then simmer until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} if needed.

Share the jasmine rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the peanut beef stir-fry.

Sprinkle over the @Roasted White Sesame Seeds{5%g} to finish.

Enjoy!